# Environment Variables Template for Railway Deployment
# Copy these to Railway → Your Service → Variables tab

# ====================================
# REQUIRED - Database Configuration
# ====================================
# Get these from: Supabase → Settings → Database → Connection String → JDBC
DB_URL=jdbc:postgresql://db.YOUR_PROJECT_ID.supabase.co:5432/postgres?sslmode=require
DB_USER=postgres.YOUR_PROJECT_ID
DB_PASS=your_supabase_database_password

# ====================================
# REQUIRED - JWT Secret
# ====================================
# Run: .\generate-jwt-secret.ps1 to generate a secure secret
JWT_SECRET=your-64-character-random-string-here

# ====================================
# REQUIRED - Spring Profile
# ====================================
SPRING_PROFILES_ACTIVE=prod

# ====================================
# OPTIONAL - Port (Railway auto-assigns)
# ====================================
PORT=8080

# ====================================
# OPTIONAL - Email Configuration
# ====================================
# For Gmail, use App Password: https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords
SMTP_USER=your-email@gmail.com
SMTP_PASS=your-gmail-app-password
SMTP_FROM=noreply@festify.com

# ====================================
# OPTIONAL - Admin Account
# ====================================
ADMIN_EMAIL=admin@festify.com
ADMIN_PASS=your-secure-admin-password

# ====================================
# HOW TO ADD IN RAILWAY
# ====================================
# 1. Go to https://railway.app
# 2. Select your project
# 3. Click on your backend service
# 4. Go to "Variables" tab
# 5. Click "New Variable" for each variable above
# 6. Paste the variable name and value
# 7. Click "Add" or "Save"
#
# OR use Railway CLI:
# railway variables set DB_URL="jdbc:postgresql://..."
# railway variables set DB_USER="postgres.xxx"
# railway variables set DB_PASS="password"
# railway variables set JWT_SECRET="your-secret"
# railway variables set SPRING_PROFILES_ACTIVE="prod"

# ====================================
# GETTING SUPABASE CREDENTIALS
# ====================================
# 1. Go to https://app.supabase.com
# 2. Select your project
# 3. Click Settings (gear icon)
# 4. Click "Database" in the sidebar
# 5. Scroll to "Connection string" section
# 6. Select "JDBC" tab
# 7. Copy the connection string
# 8. The format will be:
#    jdbc:postgresql://db.PROJECT_ID.supabase.co:5432/postgres
# 9. Add ?sslmode=require at the end
# 10. Username is usually: postgres.PROJECT_ID
# 11. Password is your database password (set during project creation)

# ====================================
# VERIFICATION
# ====================================
# After adding all variables, your service should show:
# - DB_URL (should start with jdbc:postgresql://)
# - DB_USER (should start with postgres.)
# - DB_PASS (hidden for security)
# - JWT_SECRET (hidden for security)
# - SPRING_PROFILES_ACTIVE=prod
#
# Then trigger a redeploy:
# Railway → Service → Deployments → Redeploy
